          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <supportDesc material="parchment">
                <support>
                  <p>The text of the manuscript is written in black ink. The diacritica of the script is indicated by oblique dashes. There is a second layer of dicritical marking by thin strokes, e.g. by the letter <hi rend="italic">yāʾ</hi>. Red and green dots indicate the vocalisation. Clusters of four strokes indicate the ends of the verses. A circular ornament in red, green and yellow mark the end of a group of ten verses. </p>
                </support>
